                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14702788" author="slebresne" created="Wed, 19 Aug 2015 09:56:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the simplest solution is probably to just re-introduce the use of &lt;tt&gt;Verb.RANGE_SLICE&lt;/tt&gt; for range queries so we get the proper timeout. Pushed a patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/pcmanus/cassandra/commits/10125&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; to do so. It adds a small amount of cruft but that will mostly go away once we drop backward compatibility with pre-3.0 (and it&apos;s not a big deal in the first place). I&apos;ll wait on CI to finish to make sure that patch doesn&apos;t break anything before calling this ready for review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14703095" author="slebresne" created="Wed, 19 Aug 2015 14:29:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;CI results: &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/job/pcmanus-10125-testall/2/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;utests&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/job/pcmanus-10125-dtest/2/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;dtests&lt;/a&gt;. Both looks fine so marking ready for review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14703225" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 19 Aug 2015 15:47:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=aweisberg&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;aweisberg&quot;&gt;aweisberg&lt;/a&gt; to review&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14703762" author="aweisberg" created="Wed, 19 Aug 2015 21:20:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 I think I understand it and it looks like it does what you say it does. Tests also pass.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is the plan to keep using two verbs to drive the different timeouts?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14706379" author="slebresne" created="Fri, 21 Aug 2015 08:08:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Is the plan to keep using two verbs to drive the different timeouts?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t have particular plan to change it, mostly because I don&apos;t see much drawback at using the 2 verbs (even if it&apos;s just for the timeout).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
